WEBVTT

00:02.045 --> 00:05.005
[dramatic piano music]

00:05.048 --> 00:09.052
♪

00:09.096 --> 00:11.185
[bells ringing]

00:11.228 --> 00:14.057
♪

00:14.101 --> 00:17.060
- Well, hello there.

00:17.104 --> 00:18.670
Who are you?

00:18.714 --> 00:21.499
Based on your vibe,
a student.

00:21.543 --> 00:24.067
Your blouse is loose.

00:24.111 --> 00:26.722
You're not here to be ogled,
but those bracelets,

00:26.765 --> 00:28.419
they jangle.

00:28.463 --> 00:31.640
You like a little attention.
Okay, I bite.

00:31.683 --> 00:33.468
You search the books.

00:33.511 --> 00:36.340
Uh, fiction.
F through K.

00:36.384 --> 00:39.822
Now, hmm, you're not
the standard insecure nymph

00:39.865 --> 00:42.825
hunting for Faulkner
you'll never finish.

00:42.868 --> 00:45.045
Too sun-kissed
for Stephen King.

00:45.088 --> 00:47.003
Who will you buy?

00:47.047 --> 00:48.004
♪

00:48.048 --> 00:49.788
- [gasps]
Sorry.

00:49.832 --> 00:51.964
- You sound apologetic,

00:52.008 --> 00:54.619
like you're embarrassed
to be a good girl.

00:54.663 --> 00:57.927
And you murmur
your first word to me.

00:59.146 --> 01:00.930
- Hello.

01:00.973 --> 01:02.627
Do you work here?

01:02.671 --> 01:04.238
- Guilty.

01:04.281 --> 01:05.543
Can I help you
find something?

01:05.587 --> 01:06.979
- Paula Fox?

01:07.023 --> 01:08.329
- That's a good choice.

01:08.372 --> 01:10.200
- Hmm, I feel
weirdly validated.

01:10.244 --> 01:11.549
- [laughs]

01:11.593 --> 01:12.724
Follow me.

01:16.424 --> 01:18.121
She's gonna be in here.

01:18.165 --> 01:19.688
- Celebrity authors.

01:19.731 --> 01:21.385
I thought Fox
was pretty obscure.

01:21.429 --> 01:24.693
- She is Courtney Love's
maternal grandmother.

01:24.736 --> 01:26.042
You're not expected
to know that.

01:26.086 --> 01:27.826
- Good, I didn't.

01:27.870 --> 01:29.524
- Mr. Mooney
wants anyone in here

01:29.567 --> 01:31.003
who's even
tangentially famous.

01:31.047 --> 01:32.396
He thinks it sells
more books.

01:32.440 --> 01:34.268
- That's sad--
people buying books

01:34.311 --> 01:36.270
because of what's popular,
not because they want to be

01:36.313 --> 01:39.447
moved or changed
in some way.

01:39.490 --> 01:42.014
- Yeah.
It's an epidemic.

01:42.058 --> 01:43.146
- Hmm.

01:43.190 --> 01:44.539
- Yeah, you see this guy,

01:44.582 --> 01:46.628
here with the glasses,
behind you?

01:46.671 --> 01:49.979
He just grabbed Dan Brown's
latest on the way in.

01:50.022 --> 01:52.416
So he's gonna wander around
for another, like,

01:52.460 --> 01:54.418
five or ten minutes just
to find something legitimate

01:54.462 --> 01:55.637
to buy with it.

01:55.680 --> 01:57.029
- Oh, like the cereal
guys buy

01:57.073 --> 01:58.335
when they're really there
for condoms?

01:58.379 --> 01:59.771
Only makes it
more conspicuous.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.425
Like, own your shit.

02:01.469 --> 02:04.124
If Dan Brown's your kink,
then be out about it.

02:06.952 --> 02:08.519
At the end of the day,

02:08.563 --> 02:10.869
people really are
disappointing, aren't they?

02:11.914 --> 02:14.090
- Sometimes
they surprise you.

02:14.134 --> 02:15.570
[soft music]

02:15.613 --> 02:17.572
Paula Fox, top shelf.
Do you want me to...

02:17.615 --> 02:19.356
- Oh, no, I got it.

02:19.400 --> 02:22.577
♪

02:22.620 --> 02:25.362
- Oh, are you
not wearing a bra?

02:25.406 --> 02:27.103
And you want me to notice.

02:27.147 --> 02:28.974
If this was a movie,

02:29.018 --> 02:33.196
I'd grab you and we'd go at it
right in the stacks.

02:33.240 --> 02:34.806
Have you read
her fiction?

02:34.850 --> 02:36.721
"Desperate Characters" is her--
it's her best.

02:36.765 --> 02:38.375
- Oh, that's what
I keep hearing.

02:38.419 --> 02:39.855
- You haven't read
"Desperate Characters"?

02:39.898 --> 02:41.291
- I know. I know.

02:41.335 --> 02:42.597
I'm worried it's not gonna
live up to the hype.

02:42.640 --> 02:44.425
- I can safely say
it is that good.

02:44.468 --> 02:45.948
- That's a high endorsement.

02:45.991 --> 02:48.211
And from a bookstore clerk,
nonetheless.

02:48.255 --> 02:49.908
- Well, it's
bookstore manager.

02:49.952 --> 02:52.172
- Hello?
Anyone working here?

02:53.129 --> 02:54.217
- Asshole.

02:54.261 --> 02:55.653
- Oh.

02:55.697 --> 02:57.655
Whoa.
- [laughs]

03:02.094 --> 03:03.661
- Do you mind?
Uh, I'm in a hurry.

03:03.705 --> 03:05.533
- He's just pissed
he's gotta buy Salinger

03:05.576 --> 03:07.404
to feel respectable
when all he really wants to do

03:07.448 --> 03:09.754
is eat Cheetos
and jerk it to iPorn

03:09.798 --> 03:14.063
before washing it all down
with a Dan Brown chaser.

03:14.106 --> 03:15.369
Have a nice day, sir.

03:19.503 --> 03:21.679
- Okay, I'm going for it.

03:21.723 --> 03:23.159
- Good, you won't regret it.

03:23.203 --> 03:24.291
- Better not.

03:24.334 --> 03:26.206
- Paula Fox, nice.

03:26.249 --> 03:27.816
You know, she was, uh,
Courtney Love's

03:27.859 --> 03:29.034
maternal grandmother.

03:29.078 --> 03:30.384
- That's why I'm buying it.

03:33.300 --> 03:35.563
- You have enough cash
to cover this,

03:35.606 --> 03:37.434
but you want me
to know your name.

03:37.478 --> 03:38.870
Guinevere?

03:38.914 --> 03:40.350
- Yeah, my parents
were assholes

03:40.394 --> 03:42.091
with the whole naming thing.

03:42.134 --> 03:45.442
But everyone
just calls me Beck.

03:45.486 --> 03:47.836
And you're Joe?

03:47.879 --> 03:49.925
- Goldberg.

03:49.968 --> 03:51.840
Everyone calls me Joe.

03:51.883 --> 03:53.450
- [laughs]

03:53.494 --> 03:56.105
♪

03:56.148 --> 03:57.889
- Aren't you gonna tell me
to have a nice day?

03:57.933 --> 03:59.891
- You have a nice day, Beck.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.763
- You have one yourself, Joe.

04:01.806 --> 04:05.593
♪

04:05.636 --> 04:08.813
- You smiled,
laughed at my jokes,

04:08.857 --> 04:12.687
told me your name,
asked for mine.

04:12.730 --> 04:14.602
- She write her number
on there?

04:14.645 --> 04:16.647
She was on you hard.

04:16.691 --> 04:18.475
- No, she was just being nice.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.347
- I'd be Googling the hell
out of her right now.

04:20.390 --> 04:21.783
You know her full name.

04:21.826 --> 04:23.698
- That's pretty aggressive,
Ethan.

04:23.741 --> 04:25.134
- What do I tell you?

04:25.177 --> 04:27.963
Always be closing that shit.

04:29.356 --> 04:30.661
If you need me...
- If you need me...

04:30.705 --> 04:31.706
both: I'll be in cookbooks

04:31.749 --> 04:33.098
but for work, not for fun.

04:33.142 --> 04:34.752
I swear.

04:34.796 --> 04:36.624
- At the end of the day,

04:36.667 --> 04:38.756
people are really just
disappointing, aren't they?

04:38.800 --> 04:41.759
[dramatic music]

04:41.803 --> 04:45.197
♪

04:45.241 --> 04:47.069
But are you, Beck?

04:47.112 --> 04:48.462
Are you?

04:48.505 --> 04:55.556
♪

05:01.301 --> 05:04.260
[hip-hop music
playing on car stereo]

05:04.304 --> 05:06.436
♪

05:06.480 --> 05:09.483
Yes, people find "the one."

05:09.526 --> 05:12.964
I believe that.
I try to stay open.

05:13.008 --> 05:14.488
I was in love once.

05:14.531 --> 05:16.403
She broke my heart, Beck.

05:16.446 --> 05:19.319
Oh, she really
did a number on me.

05:19.362 --> 05:21.146
I should have seen the signs.

05:21.190 --> 05:24.280
But we never do
when we're in love.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.369
Exhibit A:
Claudia and Ron.

05:26.413 --> 05:28.153
- Went out
for a couple of drinks.

05:28.197 --> 05:29.981
Get off my back, Claudia.
- [yelling indistinctly]

05:30.025 --> 05:32.462
- Claudia's a nurse.
Single parent.

05:32.506 --> 05:34.246
- It's every night!
- It's not every night!

05:34.290 --> 05:35.900
- You think she knew
Ron was a shitbag

05:35.944 --> 05:37.598
when she fell in love?

05:37.641 --> 05:39.817
No, she thought
he was a prince.

05:39.861 --> 05:41.253
Hey, Paco.

05:41.297 --> 05:43.081
- What's up, Joe?

05:43.125 --> 05:45.780
- And now hers is not
the only life she ruined.

05:45.823 --> 05:49.697
- Leave me alone!
I don't wanna talk to you!

05:49.740 --> 05:51.089
- Is everything cool in there?

05:51.133 --> 05:53.875
- Yeah, Mom and Ron
are just talking.

05:53.918 --> 05:55.442
- No, man,
this isn't your house--

05:55.485 --> 05:58.619
- Wow, you are burning
through that book, aren't you?

05:58.662 --> 06:00.011
- Reads quick.

06:00.055 --> 06:01.448
It's good.

06:01.491 --> 06:02.536
- Well, let me know
when you finish.

06:02.579 --> 06:04.320
I'll--I'll get you another one.

06:04.364 --> 06:08.498
- All right, well,
I don't care about that!

06:08.542 --> 06:09.673
- Are you hungry?

06:09.717 --> 06:11.371
- [shouting indistinctly]

06:11.414 --> 06:12.981
- 'Cause, you know, I just got
this meatball sub,

06:13.024 --> 06:15.375
but I remembered I have Thai
from last night.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.072
- [shouting indistinctly]

06:17.115 --> 06:19.379
- No, my mom will just
make me something later.

06:19.422 --> 06:20.945
- It's a shame.
This won't keep.

06:20.989 --> 06:23.034
It's getting tossed.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.340
- You sure, Joe?

06:26.429 --> 06:28.431
- All for one
and one for all.

06:41.313 --> 06:46.449
The point, Beck:
love is tricky.

06:47.711 --> 06:50.671
- ♪ Shiny, shiny

06:50.714 --> 06:55.719
♪ Shiny boots of leather

06:55.763 --> 07:01.769
♪ Whiplash girl child
in the dark ♪

07:01.812 --> 07:05.425
♪

07:05.468 --> 07:07.862
- A guy needs
to protect himself.

07:07.905 --> 07:10.517
I had to be sure you're safe.

07:10.560 --> 07:13.520
And your name was
a glorious place to start.

07:13.563 --> 07:16.479
Not a lot of Guinevere Becks.

07:16.523 --> 07:17.872
And there you were.

07:17.915 --> 07:19.613
Every account set to public.

07:19.656 --> 07:21.919
You want to be seen...

07:21.963 --> 07:24.182
heard, known.

07:24.226 --> 07:27.621
Of course, I obliged.

07:27.664 --> 07:30.928
Born and raised,
Nantucket Island.

07:30.972 --> 07:33.844
A brother, Clyde,
and sister, Anya.

07:33.888 --> 07:37.021
Your parents really were
assholes about the names.

07:37.065 --> 07:39.459
Your folks split
when you were 12.

07:39.502 --> 07:42.113
Your dad dropped out
of the picture.

07:42.157 --> 07:44.333
Went to Brown, where you
majored in lit, cool.

07:44.376 --> 07:46.596
And minored in douchebags,
mm.

07:46.640 --> 07:48.903
And then on to NYC
to conquer an MFA

07:48.946 --> 07:50.557
and make your mark,
presumably.

07:50.600 --> 07:52.733
Now, you still write.
Barely.

07:52.776 --> 07:54.299
Too busy living out moments
you won't remember

07:54.343 --> 07:55.953
five years from now.

07:55.997 --> 07:58.260
I know this because you
post about this life

07:58.303 --> 07:59.914
all the goddamn time.

07:59.957 --> 08:02.307
[indistinct chatter]

08:02.351 --> 08:04.222
Candidly, it's
the least appealing thing

08:04.266 --> 08:05.920
about you, Beck.

08:05.963 --> 08:09.010
You posted this
hours after our encounter.

08:09.053 --> 08:10.794
I was concerned.

08:10.838 --> 08:12.622
You didn't mention that
cute guy in the bookstore.

08:12.666 --> 08:15.364
And then I realized,
your online life isn't real.

08:15.407 --> 08:17.279
It's a--it's a collage.

08:17.322 --> 08:18.802
You paste this Beck up--

08:18.846 --> 08:21.239
this, uh, together,
lovable, cute,

08:21.283 --> 08:23.024
bendy little creature.

08:23.067 --> 08:24.895
If anything, the fact
that you didn't share me

08:24.939 --> 08:27.855
with your followers only
confirms we really connected.

08:27.898 --> 08:30.248
The next thing our little
friend the Internet gave me

08:30.292 --> 08:31.772
was your address.

08:31.815 --> 08:35.384
♪

08:36.951 --> 08:39.344
There it is,
with its big,

08:39.388 --> 08:41.259
naked windows.

08:41.303 --> 08:42.783
It's nice--
too nice.

08:42.826 --> 08:45.568
I'm thinking subsidized
school housing.

08:45.612 --> 08:48.353
Jesus, it's like you've never
seen a horror movie

08:48.397 --> 08:50.051
or the news.

08:50.094 --> 08:53.402
[soft dramatic music]

08:53.445 --> 08:54.403
[beep]

08:54.446 --> 08:57.580
♪

08:57.624 --> 09:00.191
But you want people to watch,
don't you?

09:00.235 --> 09:01.932
You know, I plan on asking you
about this quality

09:01.976 --> 09:03.630
when we get to know
each other better.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.414
A proposal:

09:05.457 --> 09:06.981
why don't we spend the day
together tomorrow,

09:07.024 --> 09:08.678
just you and me?

09:08.722 --> 09:10.419
- To everyone out there
chasing their dreams,

09:10.462 --> 09:11.420
don't give up.

09:11.463 --> 09:12.682
And in the meantime,

09:12.726 --> 09:15.293
Mac N Cheese!

09:15.337 --> 09:16.381
- It's cute.

09:16.425 --> 09:18.514
Not deep, but cute.

09:18.558 --> 09:20.516
Is there more to you?

09:20.560 --> 09:21.996
Let's find out.

09:22.039 --> 09:26.043
♪

09:26.087 --> 09:29.873
- ♪ You're mine

09:29.917 --> 09:32.659
♪ And we belong together

09:32.702 --> 09:34.486
- Our day starts
at the ass crack of dawn.

09:34.530 --> 09:36.271
I know from your posted
schedule that you teach

09:36.314 --> 09:39.013
a 6:30 class called
Get Up N Flow.

09:39.056 --> 09:41.668
You caress the sweaty backs
of bulimic,

09:41.711 --> 09:43.757
dead-eyed Real Mommies
of Soho...

09:43.800 --> 09:46.237
- I am loving your form
today, Tasha.

09:46.281 --> 09:48.631
- Offering smiles
and lies of encouragement.

09:48.675 --> 09:50.459
♪

09:50.502 --> 09:53.593
By 10:00, you're at campus
to TA a romantics class

09:53.636 --> 09:55.682
and play Vanna White
to some shirt.

09:55.725 --> 09:57.422
- Good morning,
Professor Leahy.

09:57.466 --> 09:59.337
- I told you, it's Paul.

09:59.381 --> 10:00.948
Are you ready for class?

10:00.991 --> 10:02.906
- Professor Obvious
wants to fuck you.

10:02.950 --> 10:04.604
But you're smart.

10:04.647 --> 10:06.518
You--you let him think
one day, he might.

10:06.562 --> 10:07.911
And what's the harm in that,
right?

10:07.955 --> 10:09.652
- ♪ Together

10:09.696 --> 10:12.437
- After class, you head
to your favorite cafe

10:12.481 --> 10:15.136
to write for the first time
all day.

10:15.179 --> 10:16.659
[cell phone buzzes]

10:16.703 --> 10:18.922
But your life
doesn't cooperate.

10:18.966 --> 10:21.185
Your wealthy girlfriends
have just now woken up

10:21.229 --> 10:23.535
and have nothing better to do
than plan their next

10:23.579 --> 10:26.016
pointless yet
Instagrammable night.

10:26.060 --> 10:27.844
Can we get real for a second?

10:27.888 --> 10:29.324
You have questionable taste
in friends, Beck...

10:29.367 --> 10:32.849
- ♪ You've been holding back

10:32.893 --> 10:35.504
♪ For a lifetime

10:35.547 --> 10:37.462
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

10:37.506 --> 10:40.422
- Oh, yes, happy birthday!

10:40.465 --> 10:41.902
[laughter]

10:41.945 --> 10:44.426
- And expensive taste
in lives.

10:44.469 --> 10:47.951
- Ready?
- Thank you.

10:47.995 --> 10:49.692
[gasps]
- Do you like it?

10:49.736 --> 10:51.346
- No, I hate it.

10:51.389 --> 10:53.000
Of course I love it!

10:53.043 --> 10:54.566
- Jason didn't even get her
something that nice,

10:54.610 --> 10:56.481
and Annika finally
let him do anal.

10:56.525 --> 10:59.136
[laughter]

10:59.180 --> 11:00.485
Please.

11:00.529 --> 11:01.661
Open my gift next and tell me

11:01.704 --> 11:03.184
how much you hate me then,
lady.

11:03.227 --> 11:06.622
- ♪ I'm not going
to let you go ♪

11:06.666 --> 11:08.493
- [gasps]

11:08.537 --> 11:09.886
A butterfly?

11:09.930 --> 11:11.192
It's my spirit animal
for the year.

11:11.235 --> 11:12.759
You remembered?

11:12.802 --> 11:14.412
- Only 'cause you wouldn't
shut up about it.

11:14.456 --> 11:16.850
- You want so badly
to be one of them.

11:16.893 --> 11:18.547
- Happy birthday.
- You guys are so beautiful.

11:18.590 --> 11:19.853
- They've got nothing
to do after this,

11:19.896 --> 11:21.376
so yeah,
they'll party till 5:00

11:21.419 --> 11:23.117
and scrape it together
tomorrow.

11:23.160 --> 11:25.423
But you can't.
You have to work for a living.

11:25.467 --> 11:27.817
- A McQueen, Beck?

11:27.861 --> 11:29.079
How much was it?

11:29.123 --> 11:30.690
- [chuckles]
It was on clearance.

11:30.733 --> 11:32.430
- They haven't put
a McQueen scarf on clearance

11:32.474 --> 11:34.476
since he hung himself in 2010.

11:34.519 --> 11:36.521
It'd be too much
even if she did deserve it,

11:36.565 --> 11:38.393
which she does not.

11:38.436 --> 11:40.700
- Hmm, not all your friends
are dumb.

11:40.743 --> 11:42.266
- You always do this.

11:42.310 --> 11:44.878
You make, like, a big gesture
that you can't afford

11:44.921 --> 11:47.576
because, I'm sorry,
you're too nice.

11:47.619 --> 11:48.708
- It's no big deal.

11:48.751 --> 11:51.972
I had, um,
a gift card.

11:52.015 --> 11:53.538
- How broke are you?

11:55.540 --> 11:57.194
Just tell me what's up.

11:57.238 --> 11:59.501
- Actually sounds
like she cares.

11:59.544 --> 12:01.198
- Look, I appreciate--

12:01.242 --> 12:03.635
- Why don't you just let me
loan you some cash, okay?

12:03.679 --> 12:05.376
I keep telling you
it's nothing.

12:05.420 --> 12:06.987
- Also sounds condescending.

12:07.030 --> 12:10.033
- You know I'd do
anything for you.

12:10.077 --> 12:12.949
Don't forget that.

12:12.993 --> 12:14.821
Sure you can't
come out with us?

12:14.864 --> 12:16.039
- I gotta write.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.867
- Virtuous.
Catch you later.

12:17.911 --> 12:20.391
- ♪ There is nothing
in this world ♪

12:20.435 --> 12:22.872
♪ That can keep me
from loving you ♪

12:22.916 --> 12:25.483
- Is that the best friend
you've got?

12:25.527 --> 12:29.052
If so, Beck,
you really are alone.

12:29.096 --> 12:33.404
- ♪ I'm gonna break down
your walls ♪

12:38.627 --> 12:41.021
- Your social media's a liar.

12:41.064 --> 12:44.764
It says you're
a happy-go-lucky dilettante.

12:44.807 --> 12:48.289
But underneath it all,
you seem like

12:48.332 --> 12:49.856
the genuine article.

12:49.899 --> 12:51.379
Stretched ADD thin, sure,

12:51.422 --> 12:52.946
but as soon
as the door closes,

12:52.989 --> 12:54.556
you're back at the keyboard,

12:54.599 --> 12:55.818
trying to write.

12:57.602 --> 12:59.953
[cell phone buzzes]

12:59.996 --> 13:04.479
[dramatic music]

13:04.522 --> 13:06.089
- [sighs]

13:06.133 --> 13:13.183
♪

13:15.577 --> 13:16.883
- Thanks.

13:16.926 --> 13:19.842
♪

