But none of this matters
because of my second

27:21.248 --> 27:23.206
and greatest discovery.

27:23.250 --> 27:26.340
11:06 a.m., an hour after our encounter at the bookstore,

27:26.383 --> 27:27.950
amidst a group text
on the merits

27:27.994 --> 27:30.910
of, uh, vaginal detoxing,
you wrote...

27:30.953 --> 27:34.522
- Wow. Just met a human male
who actually reads.

27:34.565 --> 27:36.089
Alert the media.

27:36.132 --> 27:37.612
What if it's finally
time for me

27:37.656 --> 27:39.092
to date someone
good for me?

27:39.135 --> 27:40.789
- Thank you
for letting me know

27:40.833 --> 27:42.095
I wasn't crazy after all.

27:42.138 --> 27:43.531
[door opens]
No!

27:43.574 --> 27:44.706
- Yes.

27:44.750 --> 27:45.794
I remember what you said

27:45.838 --> 27:48.057
when you sent money last.

27:48.101 --> 27:49.929
Yes, I'm grateful.

27:49.972 --> 27:51.408
♪

27:51.452 --> 27:53.541
[laughs]
I'm working constantly.

27:53.584 --> 27:56.718
There's no place cheaper
to live.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.111
I did.

27:58.154 --> 28:01.810
He basically offered
to sleep with me.

28:01.854 --> 28:03.812
No, I can't report him.
That's not how it works.

28:03.856 --> 28:05.466
- I'm not worried.

28:05.509 --> 28:07.250
I've seen enough
romantic comedies to know

28:07.294 --> 28:09.078
guys like me are always
getting in jams like this.

28:09.122 --> 28:10.558
- Not the school,
the world.

28:10.601 --> 28:12.168
That's not how the world works.

28:12.212 --> 28:13.604
♪

28:13.648 --> 28:15.215
I know how much
you helped me.

28:15.258 --> 28:17.608
It's just,
it's hard here, Mom.

28:17.652 --> 28:19.654
♪

28:19.698 --> 28:20.699
[sighs]

28:21.874 --> 28:24.833
Okay.
I'll figure it out.

28:24.877 --> 28:26.792
All right,
love you too.

28:26.835 --> 28:28.010
Bye, Mom.

28:30.796 --> 28:33.799
[crying]

28:39.021 --> 28:40.675
- It's okay, Beck.

28:41.676 --> 28:43.112
- [crying]

28:45.636 --> 28:47.073
[cell phone rings]

28:47.116 --> 28:48.552
[groans]

28:50.119 --> 28:52.861
- Hi, Becks!
- Hey, bitch, where you at?

28:52.905 --> 28:54.297
Come play!

28:54.341 --> 28:56.473
- Oh, I can't.
I just had the worst day.

28:56.517 --> 28:58.345
- Aww, Beckalicious,
whatever it is,

28:58.388 --> 29:00.042
there's nothing
that we can't fix, okay?

29:00.086 --> 29:02.088
- Yes, us and copious
amounts of alcohol.

29:02.131 --> 29:03.089
- Oh, my God.
There's a sale.

29:03.132 --> 29:04.612
- [laughs]

29:04.655 --> 29:06.092
[groans]

29:06.135 --> 29:07.789
You guys love me?

29:07.833 --> 29:09.225
- Of course!
- Why would you even say that?

29:09.269 --> 29:11.924
- Okay, then.
Meet me in Greenpoint.

29:11.967 --> 29:13.795
- Look, why don't
you come here, okay?

29:13.839 --> 29:15.101
Come here.
- It's actually really fun

29:15.144 --> 29:16.102
where we are.
I promise.

29:16.145 --> 29:17.625
- Yeah.

29:17.668 --> 29:19.670
- There's something
I need to do for myself.

29:19.714 --> 29:20.889
I'll text you on my way.

29:20.933 --> 29:22.586
- See you soon.
- Bye.

29:22.630 --> 29:23.587
[cell phone beeps]

29:23.631 --> 29:29.332
♪

29:29.376 --> 29:31.595
- I guess we're going
to Greenpoint, Beck.

29:36.775 --> 29:38.515
- ♪ So tired of feeling
this way ♪

29:38.559 --> 29:40.822
♪ Feeling like I can't go on

29:40.866 --> 29:42.389
- I never go to Greenpoint.

29:42.432 --> 29:45.696
But the things you do
for love, right?

29:45.740 --> 29:47.742
- Hi, um, okay,
so we're gonna get

29:47.786 --> 29:48.874
a few more drinks.

29:48.917 --> 29:50.266
Hold on one second.

29:50.310 --> 29:52.181
Guys?

29:52.225 --> 29:54.531
- What is she thinking?
Open mics are for

29:54.575 --> 29:56.838
models/
singer-songwriters/vegans.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.622
I mean, these people don't
wanna hear some wannabe

29:58.666 --> 30:01.016
read a poem about the bleakness
of life or whatever.

30:01.060 --> 30:03.149
- Your friends are disloyal.

30:03.192 --> 30:06.587
And that Peach is the worst.

30:06.630 --> 30:09.068
[laughter]

30:09.111 --> 30:10.852
- Another round
of picklebacks.

30:10.896 --> 30:13.942
- Beckish, do we think
now is the night?

30:13.986 --> 30:15.465
- Positive.

30:15.509 --> 30:17.380
All my life lately
has been about surviving.

30:17.424 --> 30:20.601
I need to remind myself why
I came here in the first place.

30:20.644 --> 30:21.907
- Yes!
- Yeah.

30:21.950 --> 30:23.343
- You go.
- Who do you keep texting?

30:23.386 --> 30:25.693
- I invited Benji.
- Beck.

30:25.736 --> 30:27.869
- What?
He likes poetry.

30:27.913 --> 30:29.610
- For sure.
- And he texted he was coming?

30:29.653 --> 30:33.222
- He texted a row
of smile emojis, like,

30:33.266 --> 30:34.920
45 minutes ago.

30:34.963 --> 30:36.138
- Some guys are assholes,

30:36.182 --> 30:37.400
and you just have
to realize that.

30:37.444 --> 30:39.098
- I get it, Peach.

30:39.141 --> 30:40.403
- No, you're the one who
told me to keep reminding you

30:40.447 --> 30:41.883
he's a bastard.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.930
- Up next, we have
Guinevere Beck.

30:44.973 --> 30:46.279
- Whoo!

30:46.322 --> 30:47.671
- All right.
- All right.

30:47.715 --> 30:50.413
- To vulnerability and shit.

30:50.457 --> 30:51.501
- Yeah.

30:51.545 --> 30:52.938
Cheers.
- Okay.

30:52.981 --> 30:54.853
- Okay.
- Okay.

30:54.896 --> 30:56.028
- Kill it, Beck.

30:57.507 --> 31:00.815
- Hey, everyone, um,
I'm Beck,

31:00.859 --> 31:03.687
and I'm--not to sound like,
you know, whatever,

31:03.731 --> 31:06.777
but just--
I'm a--I'm a poet.

31:06.821 --> 31:08.518
- Yeah, you are!

31:08.562 --> 31:09.911
Whoo!

31:09.955 --> 31:11.130
- Yeah, you are!

31:12.566 --> 31:16.091
- One day, you won't
need love anymore.

31:16.135 --> 31:18.615
One day, you won't
walk through the world

31:18.659 --> 31:21.836
as though it was your job
to hold everything up.

31:21.880 --> 31:25.361
The sun,
the hard part of the night,

31:25.405 --> 31:28.408
the secret time when you wake
to the sound of beating,

31:28.451 --> 31:31.237
rise to answer the door,
but he's not there

31:31.280 --> 31:33.717
because that sound
is coming from inside you.

31:33.761 --> 31:37.156
And you cannot answer it
no matter how far in you go.

31:37.199 --> 31:40.072
- Wrap it up!

31:40.115 --> 31:43.031
[dramatic music]

31:43.075 --> 31:44.163
- Whoo!

31:44.206 --> 31:45.904
- You loved him the way

31:45.947 --> 31:49.211
fragile kids
love gorgeous bullies.

31:49.255 --> 31:53.172
You wrote songs about him--
uh, I mean...

31:53.215 --> 31:56.349
[laughs]
You wrote poems about him.

31:56.392 --> 31:58.960
You still write poems
about him.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.093
You're writing one right now.

32:01.136 --> 32:02.964
- Why are you so sad?

32:03.008 --> 32:04.966
Just so sad.

32:05.010 --> 32:08.317
Just something happier
for a change might be nice.

32:08.361 --> 32:10.450
I think everyone agrees.

32:10.493 --> 32:11.930
Can we get the singer back?

32:11.973 --> 32:12.931
She was--

32:12.974 --> 32:14.410
- Sorry, I, uh--

32:14.454 --> 32:16.108
I just, um--I lost my place.

32:16.151 --> 32:18.284
It'll just take a second
to find where I was.

32:18.327 --> 32:19.807
- I can't stand seeing this.

32:19.850 --> 32:22.418
I'm sorry.
I-I just can't.

32:22.462 --> 32:23.811
It's obvious what you are.

32:23.854 --> 32:25.247
You're blind with love.

32:25.291 --> 32:27.119
And what you love--
writing,

32:27.162 --> 32:28.598
this city,
your friends,

32:28.642 --> 32:30.078
most of all, men like Benji--

32:30.122 --> 32:31.732
what all those
have in common is,

32:31.775 --> 32:33.647
they will never love you back,

32:33.690 --> 32:35.127
while you give everything.

32:35.170 --> 32:36.476
♪

32:36.519 --> 32:37.738
It's crazy, the lengths we go.

32:37.781 --> 32:40.045
We're a lot alike, Beck.

32:40.088 --> 32:41.916
Last of the true romantics.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.223
♪

32:44.266 --> 32:48.140
- ♪ Engine number nine

32:48.183 --> 32:52.013
♪ On the New York Transit line

32:52.057 --> 32:53.710
♪ If my train...

32:53.754 --> 32:55.190
- I was considering this
with my new friend,

32:55.234 --> 32:57.062
Mr. Batshit Homeless Guy,

32:57.105 --> 32:59.629
when the second luckiest thing
this week happened.

32:59.673 --> 33:01.892
♪

33:01.936 --> 33:03.677
Could it really be?

33:03.720 --> 33:05.940
It feels like I'm dreaming.

33:05.984 --> 33:08.769
- ♪ Pick it up

33:08.812 --> 33:11.206
- I'm not.
- ♪ Pick it up

33:11.250 --> 33:13.208
- Beck, you're too drunk
to be alone.

33:13.252 --> 33:16.081
What if some sicko
had followed you down here?

33:16.124 --> 33:17.691
And you're too wasted
to be standing so close

33:17.734 --> 33:19.301
to the tracks.
Beck!

33:19.345 --> 33:21.477
Beck, stop texting
that arrogant club soda

33:21.521 --> 33:23.349
no-show dickhead.

33:23.392 --> 33:26.004
- ♪ New York line

33:26.047 --> 33:30.443
♪ If my train
jump off the track ♪

33:30.486 --> 33:32.053
- You want Benji.

33:32.097 --> 33:34.751
- ♪ Pick it up, pick it up,
pick it up ♪

33:34.795 --> 33:36.231
- You need Benji.

33:36.275 --> 33:38.059
You hold that phone
like it is Benji

33:38.103 --> 33:40.409
'cause it's your only means
to stay connected.

33:40.453 --> 33:42.672
Forget Benji.

33:42.716 --> 33:43.891
[cell phone buzzes]

33:43.934 --> 33:46.372
And to hell with that phone!

33:46.415 --> 33:48.809
- [grunts]
- Pick it up. Pick it up.

33:48.852 --> 33:51.377
Pick it up. Pick it up.
- [coughing]

33:51.420 --> 33:54.771
- ♪ Engine, engine number nine

33:54.815 --> 33:56.251
- [gasping]

33:56.295 --> 33:59.428
- ♪ On the New York
Transit line ♪

33:59.472 --> 34:00.864
- Hey, hey, hey!

34:00.908 --> 34:02.083
You okay?

34:02.127 --> 34:03.650
Are you all right?
Can you stand up?

34:03.693 --> 34:05.391
Just stay still.

34:05.434 --> 34:07.132
Half that shit down there
can electrocute you, all right?

34:07.175 --> 34:08.698
So just give me your hand.

34:08.742 --> 34:10.222
- Pick it up. Pick it up.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

34:10.265 --> 34:11.223
Pick it up. Pick it up!

34:11.266 --> 34:12.659
- Sir, please shut up!

34:12.702 --> 34:13.790
- Pick it up!
- Give me your hand.

34:13.834 --> 34:15.531
- The train's coming.

34:15.575 --> 34:17.185
- Pick it up. Pick it up.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

34:17.229 --> 34:18.491
Pick it up. Pick it up.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

34:18.534 --> 34:21.407
[train clacking]

34:21.450 --> 34:22.973
- Your hand, now!

34:23.017 --> 34:24.105
- Pick it up!

34:24.149 --> 34:25.759
- [grunts]
- Pick it up!

34:25.802 --> 34:27.587
[train whistle blows]

34:27.630 --> 34:30.590
[dramatic music]

34:30.633 --> 34:36.074
♪

34:36.117 --> 34:37.118
- [vomits]

34:43.472 --> 34:44.517
- [groans]

34:44.560 --> 34:46.475
- Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

34:46.519 --> 34:47.737
- Whoo!
- I am so sorry.

34:47.781 --> 34:48.999
- No, it's fine.
It's fine.

34:49.043 --> 34:52.177
I, uh--I hated--
I hated this jacket.

34:52.220 --> 34:54.570
- I really am sorry.

34:54.614 --> 34:56.094
- It's okay.

34:56.137 --> 34:57.182
- Do you mind?

34:58.574 --> 34:59.532
[sighs]

34:59.575 --> 35:00.968
- Sure, um...

35:04.102 --> 35:06.234
You know what? Let's get you
in a cab, all right?

35:09.194 --> 35:11.239
- I'm not always like this.

35:13.981 --> 35:16.070
- I figured you had
some kinda night.

35:16.114 --> 35:18.116
- Some kinda...

35:20.553 --> 35:23.425
Hey, I don't wanna sound
like a stalker, but...

35:24.861 --> 35:26.515
I think I know you.

35:26.559 --> 35:28.256
Paula Fox?

35:29.431 --> 35:30.780
- Oh, right, right!

35:30.824 --> 35:31.912
Of course.

35:31.955 --> 35:34.219
I remember.
I'm sorry.

35:34.262 --> 35:36.569
- This is what I look like
when I'm sober

35:36.612 --> 35:37.744
and have my hair up.

35:37.787 --> 35:40.181
- Yeah, no,
I remember.

35:40.225 --> 35:43.358
- It's okay.
I have a pretty bland face.

35:43.402 --> 35:44.577
- No, you don't.

35:47.319 --> 35:49.016
Yeah, uh,
"Desperate Characters."

35:49.059 --> 35:50.844
I remember.

35:50.887 --> 35:52.411
- Yeah.

35:53.238 --> 35:54.326
- Where you headed?

35:54.369 --> 35:55.631
- Village.

35:55.675 --> 35:57.459
Are you anywhere close?

35:57.503 --> 35:58.678
Ride with me.

35:58.721 --> 36:00.375
It's the least I can do.

36:00.419 --> 36:02.638
[dramatic music]

36:02.682 --> 36:03.639
- Okay.

36:03.683 --> 36:10.733
♪

36:16.174 --> 36:18.045
- Did you move here
to be something?

36:18.088 --> 36:19.742
I did,
but it's not working out,

36:19.786 --> 36:21.831
and I'm just running around
18 hours a day.

36:21.875 --> 36:23.093
Why?

36:23.137 --> 36:25.487
♪

36:25.531 --> 36:27.576
Oh, God, never mind.
Sorry.

36:27.620 --> 36:29.404
- No, please.

36:29.448 --> 36:31.928
I feel the same way
sometimes.

36:31.972 --> 36:34.366
This guy I know,
he owns the bookstore.

36:34.409 --> 36:36.672
He once told me
that all books

36:36.716 --> 36:40.937
add up to one
essential truth,

36:40.981 --> 36:43.766
which is, if your IQ is above
a certain number...

36:43.810 --> 36:45.638
♪

36:45.681 --> 36:47.248
Life is pretty much
unbearable.

36:47.292 --> 36:49.511
And the number
is not even that high.

36:49.555 --> 36:51.644
♪

36:51.687 --> 36:54.864
- I do think I'd be happier
if I was stupider.

36:54.908 --> 36:56.431
- [laughs]

36:56.475 --> 36:58.259
But then the world
wouldn't know your poetry.

36:58.303 --> 37:00.435
- How'd you know
I write poetry?

37:00.479 --> 37:03.395
♪

37:03.438 --> 37:06.398
- Doesn't every young writer
in New York?

37:06.441 --> 37:08.051
I mean, I read
a lot of poetry.

37:08.095 --> 37:10.663
♪

37:10.706 --> 37:12.839
- Who do you like?

37:12.882 --> 37:15.450
- Strand, Sexton, Merrill.

37:15.494 --> 37:18.192
- You're describing
my nightstand.

37:18.236 --> 37:21.326
- Well, if you read them
to get to sleep every night,

37:21.369 --> 37:23.415
then you definitely
belong here.

37:23.458 --> 37:25.286
- [chuckles]

37:25.330 --> 37:27.288
What was your last name again?

37:27.332 --> 37:28.507
- Goldberg.

37:28.550 --> 37:30.030
♪

37:30.073 --> 37:32.946
- Where did you come from,
Joe Goldberg?

37:32.989 --> 37:34.426
- I grew up here.

37:34.469 --> 37:36.471
♪

37:36.515 --> 37:38.299
I left for a little while,

37:38.343 --> 37:39.474
chasing a girl.

37:39.518 --> 37:41.520
- Mm, but you came back?

37:41.563 --> 37:43.913
- Yeah, I missed it.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.567
And I'm not a good chaser.

37:45.611 --> 37:48.048
- Hmm, me neither.

37:48.091 --> 37:55.142
♪

38:05.500 --> 38:06.849
Oh.

38:08.721 --> 38:11.637
Oh, this is, uh...
this is me.

38:11.680 --> 38:14.248
- Mm, it's not bad.

38:14.292 --> 38:17.338
- Thank you for sobering me up.

38:17.382 --> 38:19.122
And for saving my life.

38:19.166 --> 38:21.560
- No, I didn't--
I didn't save your life.

38:21.603 --> 38:22.778
- Yeah, you did.

38:22.822 --> 38:29.872
♪

38:30.351 --> 38:32.658
[knocking]

38:32.701 --> 38:34.442
Oh, God.

38:34.486 --> 38:36.401
- Of course.

38:36.444 --> 38:38.185
Benji.
- Hi.

38:38.228 --> 38:39.969
Um, this is Joe.

38:40.013 --> 38:42.624
He literally
saved my life tonight.

38:42.668 --> 38:44.496
I-I fell on the tracks.

38:44.539 --> 38:45.975
It was crazy.

38:46.019 --> 38:49.283
- Babe, I told you,
people are basically good.

38:49.327 --> 38:50.632
It's a great job, bro.

38:50.676 --> 38:53.374
- Bro?
You waste of hair.

38:53.418 --> 38:55.985
- Okay, Beck,
it's freezing out here.

39:00.425 --> 39:03.253
- Wait, uh, maybe I can
get your info.

39:03.297 --> 39:05.560
- Yeah, um...

39:09.129 --> 39:12.959
Shit, my phone.

39:14.177 --> 39:15.657
I must have dropped it
in the subway.

39:15.701 --> 39:17.485
- Oh.

39:17.529 --> 39:20.749
Oh, okay, well, um,
just maybe give me your number

39:20.793 --> 39:22.664
for when you get a replacement?

39:22.708 --> 39:25.188
- I'm basically
enslaved to email.

39:25.232 --> 39:27.060
- I get it. Smart.

39:27.103 --> 39:29.149
I'm practically a stranger.
Can't be too careful.

39:29.192 --> 39:30.411
Okay.

39:30.455 --> 39:34.110
- It's
beckinreallife@gmail.com.

39:34.154 --> 39:35.677
- All right.

39:35.721 --> 39:37.549
♪

39:37.592 --> 39:39.246
Beck in real life.

39:39.289 --> 39:40.682
- Thank you.

39:40.726 --> 39:44.686
♪

39:44.730 --> 39:46.209
- So here's what I learned
this week.

39:46.253 --> 39:47.646
- I'm sorry I didn't make it.
You know.

39:47.689 --> 39:49.822
- You are special.
You're talented.

39:49.865 --> 39:52.215
You're passionate.

39:52.259 --> 39:53.434
You're smart...

39:53.478 --> 39:56.176
♪

39:56.219 --> 39:58.700
Except in the ways
you're really not,

39:58.744 --> 40:00.441
like not locking your phone

40:00.485 --> 40:02.443
and falling for men
like Benji.

40:02.487 --> 40:05.925
You know better,
but you can't stop because...

40:05.968 --> 40:07.796
well, because everyone
needs someone.

40:07.840 --> 40:09.668
What you really need
is someone to save you.

40:09.711 --> 40:11.800
I can help, Beck.

40:11.844 --> 40:12.888
Let me help you.

40:19.242 --> 40:20.374
- Joe.

40:20.418 --> 40:23.246
[dramatic music]

40:23.290 --> 40:24.857
- Pac, hey.

40:24.900 --> 40:26.685
What's going on?
What are you doing out here?

40:26.728 --> 40:29.252
- It's Ron.

40:29.296 --> 40:31.777
He came home drunk.

40:31.820 --> 40:33.779
He started yelling,

40:33.822 --> 40:35.476
saying I thought I was smart,

40:35.520 --> 40:37.913
reading my books and looking
at him like he's dumb.

40:37.957 --> 40:39.698
- What--what happened?

40:39.741 --> 40:41.395
Did he hurt you?

40:41.439 --> 40:43.179
- No, he didn't touch me.

40:43.223 --> 40:50.273
♪

40:53.102 --> 40:55.061
I tried to stop him.

40:55.104 --> 40:56.497
I'm sorry.

40:56.541 --> 40:59.761
- Paco, Paco,
it's okay.

40:59.805 --> 41:01.110
Really, it's okay.

41:01.154 --> 41:02.460
You know what?
Come with me.

41:02.503 --> 41:04.157
We can fix this together,
all right?

41:04.200 --> 41:10.380
♪

41:10.424 --> 41:12.121
So, you know, the first step
to fixing something

41:12.165 --> 41:15.255
is to know no matter
how destroyed it seems,

41:15.298 --> 41:16.909
it can always be saved.

41:18.171 --> 41:20.739
Books are no exception.

41:20.782 --> 41:21.783
You got it?

41:21.827 --> 41:23.176
- Got it.

41:23.219 --> 41:25.570
- So what we have here
is a line press.

41:25.613 --> 41:27.572
Basically just a huge clamp.

41:27.615 --> 41:31.271
Polyvinyl acetate glue means
no acid to burn the pages.

41:31.314 --> 41:34.796
Got your needle, thread,
and finally--

41:34.840 --> 41:37.625
right out of "Bugs Bunny"--

41:37.669 --> 41:38.626
a trusty mallet.

41:38.670 --> 41:40.585
[dark music]

41:40.628 --> 41:41.586
You see this?

41:41.629 --> 41:43.283
♪

41:43.326 --> 41:44.589
[book rips]

41:44.632 --> 41:45.720
We don't need this.

41:45.764 --> 41:49.942
♪

41:49.985 --> 41:51.639
- Johno, listen to this!

41:51.683 --> 41:53.815
"Dear Benji,
heard about your soda.

41:53.859 --> 41:55.121
"I'm interested
in including you

41:55.164 --> 41:56.731
"on my fall list
of must-tries.

41:56.775 --> 41:58.385
"Would love to discuss,
perhaps even try some.

41:58.428 --> 41:59.865
Jeff Pevensey."

41:59.908 --> 42:01.388
- That's the dude
you're always retweeting?

42:01.431 --> 42:03.521
- It's the culture guy
from "New York" magazine.

42:03.564 --> 42:05.261
♪

42:05.305 --> 42:07.089
- Hit him back, bro.

42:07.133 --> 42:08.526
- No shit.

42:08.569 --> 42:10.049
Back off while I think.

42:10.092 --> 42:12.051
Jeff, comma,

42:12.094 --> 42:14.619
so nice to hear from you, bud,
period.

42:14.662 --> 42:16.838
Yeah, our sodas are legit,
period.

42:16.882 --> 42:18.231
I would love to meet up

42:18.274 --> 42:20.973
to have you try the goods,
period.

42:21.016 --> 42:22.278
Let's set something up.

42:22.322 --> 42:27.022
♪

42:27.066 --> 42:29.808
- Scrape carefully
along the spine.

42:29.851 --> 42:32.114
Of course,
you gotta watch your fingers.

42:32.158 --> 42:34.552
♪

42:34.595 --> 42:36.510
[cell phone buzzes]

42:36.554 --> 42:38.164
♪

42:38.207 --> 42:40.035
- "Sounds great.
I can call between meetings

42:40.079 --> 42:41.863
to see if you're available."

42:41.907 --> 42:44.518
- This is gonna take us
next level.

42:44.562 --> 42:45.693
What time you think
we'll meet?

42:45.737 --> 42:47.913
♪

42:47.956 --> 42:50.480
- No offense.
We discussed this.

42:50.524 --> 42:52.700
It's best if the product
has one clear face

42:52.744 --> 42:53.875
at the beginning.

42:53.919 --> 42:55.616
That's just more me.

42:55.660 --> 42:58.619
♪

42:58.663 --> 43:00.403
- Okay, the spine is sewn.

43:00.447 --> 43:01.622
So take this.

43:01.666 --> 43:02.754
Pull it as tight
as you can that way.

43:02.797 --> 43:04.103
♪

43:04.146 --> 43:06.061
Yeah, that's it.

43:06.105 --> 43:13.155
♪

43:14.679 --> 43:16.202
- Jeff!

43:16.245 --> 43:19.205
- The glue is set.
We've applied the binder.

43:19.248 --> 43:20.598
Now...

43:20.641 --> 43:22.295
♪

43:22.338 --> 43:24.340
You gotta be precise

43:24.384 --> 43:26.647
and use exactly
the force needed.

43:26.691 --> 43:30.695
♪

43:30.738 --> 43:33.698
[tapping]

43:35.961 --> 43:38.528
[pounding]

43:38.572 --> 43:39.529
Hey!

43:39.573 --> 43:41.488
♪

43:41.531 --> 43:42.794
- Nice to meet you, man.

43:42.837 --> 43:44.230
- Nice to meet you too.

43:44.273 --> 43:45.884
Have you--
have you been here before?

43:45.927 --> 43:48.669
It's, uh--not a lot of people
know about it yet.

43:48.713 --> 43:52.107
It's an incredible after hours.
Very exclusive.

43:52.151 --> 43:54.632
- Yeah, I've been here
a couple of times.

43:54.675 --> 43:55.937
- Yeah?
- Mm.

43:55.981 --> 43:58.940
- Huh.
Well, good.

43:58.984 --> 44:01.203
So you'll feel
right at home, then.

44:01.247 --> 44:08.167
♪

44:08.210 --> 44:11.039
Please, after you.

44:11.083 --> 44:13.302
- All right.
[chuckles]

44:13.346 --> 44:16.871
♪

44:16.915 --> 44:19.744
- It's just down to the left.

44:19.787 --> 44:26.838
♪

44:32.974 --> 44:35.890
- Hey, man,
I'm thinking maybe--

44:35.934 --> 44:36.891
[thwack]

44:36.935 --> 44:38.632
[bottles shatter]

44:38.676 --> 44:45.683
♪

44:53.734 --> 44:56.694
[soft music]

44:56.737 --> 44:58.217
♪

44:58.260 --> 45:00.001
- It's 2:00 p.m.
when the door chimes,

45:00.045 --> 45:01.916
and I'm ready.

45:01.960 --> 45:03.657
- [speaking indistinctly]

45:03.701 --> 45:05.528
- You told your girlfriends
you'd come by.

45:05.572 --> 45:07.574
I know this because
I have your phone.

45:07.617 --> 45:09.663
- I'll be in back.
- Okay.

45:09.707 --> 45:11.012
- Hey.

45:11.056 --> 45:12.361
Remember me?

45:12.405 --> 45:15.538
Almost dying
on the train tracks?

45:15.582 --> 45:17.627
- Uh, it rings a bell.

45:17.671 --> 45:19.064
Hang on. Hang on.
- [laughs]

45:19.107 --> 45:21.631
Well, I wanted
to say thank you.

45:21.675 --> 45:23.459
- No, you already did that.

45:23.503 --> 45:26.549
- Well, uh, thanks again.
[laughs]

45:26.593 --> 45:30.466
And I'm sorry for, uh,
running off the other night.

45:31.163 --> 45:32.251
- You had a guest.

45:32.294 --> 45:33.339
- Hardly.

45:34.862 --> 45:37.604
So I got you a present.

45:37.647 --> 45:38.953
- No, no, no, please.

45:38.997 --> 45:39.998
You don't have
to get me anything.

45:40.041 --> 45:41.782
- Shut up and just look at it.

45:43.436 --> 45:47.179
[dramatic music]

45:47.222 --> 45:49.790
- "Engine, engine number nine
on the New York Transit line.

45:49.834 --> 45:51.966
"If your girl
falls on the track,

45:52.010 --> 45:53.446
pick her up, pick her up,
pick her up."

45:53.489 --> 45:55.796
We already have in jokes.

45:55.840 --> 45:59.191
- So...

45:59.234 --> 46:01.802
anyway, that, and I'd better--

46:01.846 --> 46:05.632
- Maybe if you're not too busy,

46:05.675 --> 46:07.765
we could get a drink sometime?

46:07.808 --> 46:09.854
- Sure.

46:09.897 --> 46:12.117
Oh, but I still
can't find my phone.

46:12.160 --> 46:15.076
- I know.
Email.

46:15.120 --> 46:16.469
- That's right.

46:16.512 --> 46:20.125
♪

46:20.168 --> 46:21.822
See you, Joe.

46:21.866 --> 46:24.390
- See you soon, Beck.

46:24.433 --> 46:31.266
♪

46:31.310 --> 46:34.139
- Well played, sir.

46:34.182 --> 46:36.097
Well played.

46:37.403 --> 46:38.752
- I'm not always right.

46:38.796 --> 46:40.058
I'm human.
I make mistakes.

46:40.101 --> 46:41.581
You'll see.

46:41.624 --> 46:43.539
I have to check
on a shipment downstairs.

46:43.583 --> 46:45.150
Can you--um,
can you watch the register?

46:45.193 --> 46:46.151
- Yeah.

46:46.194 --> 46:47.761
[door opens]

46:47.805 --> 46:51.112
- Hell, maybe I'm just
a fool in love.

46:51.156 --> 46:53.158
But I'm right about you.

46:53.201 --> 46:56.204
And I'm going to help you get
the life you deserve, Beck.

46:56.248 --> 47:01.079
♪

47:01.122 --> 47:02.384
- [groans]

47:02.428 --> 47:05.387
[gasping]

47:05.431 --> 47:11.524
♪

47:11.567 --> 47:15.702
Please,
whatever you think I did,

47:15.745 --> 47:17.530
you got the wrong guy.

47:17.573 --> 47:20.620
- No...

47:20.663 --> 47:22.230
I don't.

47:22.274 --> 47:25.233
[tense music]

47:25.277 --> 47:26.321
♪
